# ---- OS / editors ----
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.idea/
.vscode/
*.iml
*.swp

# ---- Frontend Vite/React source (bundle output is committed) ----
# frontend/index.html is the bundled artifact (committed). The Vite source
# project under frontend/app/ generates it via the web-artifacts-builder skill;
# its node_modules + build caches do not belong in git.
frontend/app/node_modules/
frontend/app/dist/
frontend/app/.parcel-cache/
frontend/app/bundle.html

# ---- Claude Code local state ----
# The whole .claude/ directory is per-user (settings, launch config,
# scheduled-task lockfiles, session logs, slash commands).
.claude/

# ---- Java / Maven ----
core-api/target/
core-api/.mvn/wrapper/maven-wrapper.jar
core-api/build/
core-api/out/
core-api/**/*.class
core-api/logs/
core-api/HELP.md

# ---- Python ----
ai-worker/.venv/
ai-worker/venv/
ai-worker/__pycache__/
ai-worker/**/__pycache__/
ai-worker/**/*.pyc
ai-worker/.pytest_cache/
ai-worker/.mypy_cache/
ai-worker/*.egg-info/
# Pytest also runs from the repo root in some flows (e.g. when the
# user picks the workspace as basetemp). The artifacts are pure cache
# / fixture scratch — never committed.
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.tmp/
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc

# ---- Scratch tests / scripts / harnesses ----
# Forward-looking patterns: anything matching is treated as personal
# scratch and stays out of git. Promote a file to a real name (drop
# the prefix / suffix) when you want it tracked.
**/test_scratch_*.py
**/scratch_*.py
**/_scratch_*.py
**/_tmp_*.py
**/tmp_*.py
**/*_scratch.py
**/*_sandbox.py
# Non-Python scratch extensions seen in practice — interactive
# debugging dumps (lookup tables, page snapshots, intermediate
# selection lists). The repo-root prefix ``_scratch_`` is the
# convention so these don't collide with real project artefacts.
**/_scratch_*.json
**/_scratch_*.jsonl
**/_scratch_*.txt
**/_scratch_*.md
ai-worker/scripts/_scratch/
ai-worker/scripts/_drafts/
ai-worker/eval/harness/_scratch/
ai-worker/eval/harness/_drafts/
ai-worker/tests/_scratch/
ai-worker/tests/_drafts/

# ---- Eval harness generated artifacts ----
# Reports change every run and should not be committed. Sample OCR
# fixture images are synthesized by scripts/make_ocr_sample_fixtures.py
# and drift across fonts, so they are regenerated on demand. Phase-0
# baseline reports are the one exception — they anchor the README
# benchmark table and later phases diff against them.
ai-worker/eval/reports/*
!ai-worker/eval/reports/phase0/
ai-worker/eval/reports/phase0/*
!ai-worker/eval/reports/phase0/baseline.json
!ai-worker/eval/reports/phase0/baseline-anime.json
# Phase 8 agent-loop decision: the markdown + backing JSON are the
# record of the measured A/B, not a run-to-run report.
!ai-worker/eval/reports/phase8/
ai-worker/eval/reports/phase8/*
!ai-worker/eval/reports/phase8/agent_loop_decision.md
!ai-worker/eval/reports/phase8/agent_loop_decision.json
# Phase 2A reranker summary artifacts — small, deterministic, anchor
# the README benchmark table. We commit the flat candidate-recall /
# comparison / failure-analysis files; the per-run retrieval dirs
# (top_k_dump.jsonl, miss_analysis, duplicate_analysis) stay local
# because they're large and reproducible from corpus + dataset.
!ai-worker/eval/reports/phase2/
ai-worker/eval/reports/phase2/*
!ai-worker/eval/reports/phase2/2a_reranker/
ai-worker/eval/reports/phase2/2a_reranker/*
!ai-worker/eval/reports/phase2/2a_reranker/candidate-recall-b2.json
!ai-worker/eval/reports/phase2/2a_reranker/candidate-recall-b2.md
!ai-worker/eval/reports/phase2/2a_reranker/reranker-comparison.json
!ai-worker/eval/reports/phase2/2a_reranker/reranker-comparison.md
!ai-worker/eval/reports/phase2/2a_reranker/reranker-failure-analysis.json
!ai-worker/eval/reports/phase2/2a_reranker/reranker-failure-analysis.md
# Locked legacy retrieval baseline — the A/B reference for LangGraph
# adoption. Files are deterministic post-process output of
# scripts/build_legacy_baseline_final.py (no top_k_dump or per-row
# JSON, only the consolidated metrics + manifest + README).
!ai-worker/eval/reports/legacy-baseline-final/
ai-worker/eval/reports/legacy-baseline-final/*
!ai-worker/eval/reports/legacy-baseline-final/README.md
!ai-worker/eval/reports/legacy-baseline-final/metrics.json
!ai-worker/eval/reports/legacy-baseline-final/metrics.md
!ai-worker/eval/reports/legacy-baseline-final/latency_breakdown.json
!ai-worker/eval/reports/legacy-baseline-final/latency_breakdown.md
!ai-worker/eval/reports/legacy-baseline-final/selected_config.json
!ai-worker/eval/reports/legacy-baseline-final/baseline_manifest.json
# Phase 7.0 retrieval-title A/B — commit the small decision artefacts
# (final report, A/B summary, diff report, improved/regressed/per-query
# JSONL, manifest digests, generated silver query set). The two
# rag_chunks_<variant>.jsonl exports (~318 MB each) are
